// Chat Store
// Zustand store for managing chat messages from Claude's render_ui calls.
// Handles blocking UI prompts (require a response) and non-blocking notifications.

State shape:
  messages: ChatMessage[]  (max 50, newest first)
  isOpen: boolean  (drawer visibility)
  unreadCount: number
  currentBlockingId: string | null  (ID of the active blocking message)

Each ChatMessage has: id, type ('ui_render' | 'notification'), ui, blocking, timestamp, responded, response, project, session, canceled.

FUNCTION addMessage(msg)                                                EXPORT
  IF a message with the same ID already exists, ignore (deduplication).
  IF the new message is blocking, mark all existing unresponded blocking messages as canceled.
  Prepend the message, keeping at most 50 messages total.
  IF blocking: auto-open the drawer and set currentBlockingId to this message's ID.
  ELSE IF not yet responded: increment unreadCount.

---

FUNCTION respondToMessage(id, response) -> Promise<void>               EXPORT
  Find the message by ID. IF not found, return.
  POST to /api/ui-response with the message's project/session params, uiId, action, and data.
  On success: mark the message as responded and store the response.
  IF this was the currentBlockingId, clear currentBlockingId.

---

FUNCTION markAsRead(id)                                                 EXPORT
  IF the message exists, is not responded, and is not blocking: decrement unreadCount (floored at 0).

---

FUNCTION setOpen(open)                                                  EXPORT
  Set isOpen.
  IF opening: reset unreadCount to 0 (all visible messages considered read).

---

FUNCTION clearMessages()                                                EXPORT
  Reset messages, unreadCount, and currentBlockingId to initial state.

---

FUNCTION restoreUIFromCache(cachedUI, project, session)                 EXPORT
  IF a message with cachedUI.uiId already exists: update its responded/canceled status and fill in project/session if missing.
  ELSE: create a new message from the cached UI data and prepend it.
  IF the cached UI is blocking and pending: auto-open the drawer and set currentBlockingId.
